The paper deals with the characterization of Generalized Degrees of Freedom (GDoF) for a symmetric K-user MIMO Interference Channel (IC) under the assumption of limited channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT) with finite precision. This involves the study of information theory, networking, and communication systems, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.COM (Computers and Society). The paper also deals with the use of multiple antennas and interference alignment, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Among these sub-categories, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely as they are directly related to the main focus of the paper, while cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.COM are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
